{
  "stem": "13395.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They would go to a non-Jewish store.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my parents felt it, yes, very much in the business.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because if they wanted to keep the job in the German coal mine, they could not buy merchandise from us.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So this was the only change.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Otherwise, we did not feel other changes.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The people still were the same as they were before, just a fear that they would lose the job.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And of course, they have to make a living to support their families.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In Germany, the children were brainwashed in schools to tell, in school, everything that goes on in their homes.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So the children spied on their parents.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And very often, it resulted that parents were taken to Dachau or Buchenwald for subversion, because the children would overhear something or would know that their parents still associate, secretly, with Jewish friends.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They would tell the teacher in school.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, first of all, after the Kristallnacht, when they took all the Jewish-- not all, but thousands and thousands of Jewish males.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that's when they put them to camps like Buchenwald and Dachau.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The only way to get out of Dachau or Buchenwald was if you had a visa to emigrate.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And so it was mad rush on all the consulates-- South America, South Africa, United States, Canada.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we, of course, know the track record of these countries that had no room for Jews.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Children were being sent out to England.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Jews desperately tried to get out, but there was no way.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "My relatives got on that boat, which was turned away from Cuba and came back to Germany.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There was really no way for the German Jews to leave.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
